<h1>Problem 1320 - 2012 IMO, P2 of 6</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(n\ge 3\) be an integer, and let \(a_2,a_3,\ldots ,a_n\) be positive real numbers such that \(a_{2}a_{3}\cdots a_{n}=1\). Prove that
\[(1 + a_2)^2 (1 + a_3)^3 \dotsm (1 + a_n)^n > n^n.\]</p>
